The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to clustering graphs, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of parameterized complexity suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The focus on graph clustering also suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of combinatorial techniques and analysis of the structure of the problems suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
